{"title":"PCP Pneumocystis iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/PCP Pneumocystis iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Neumonía por\\NPneumocystis jirovecii\\N(PCP)","guid":"mZChRmLBXSpoPeZTOl8ZnA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"El Patógeno","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Hongo oportunista (antes P. carinii → renombrado 2002)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"ATÍPICO → no crece en cultivos fúngicos rutinarios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Pared celular con COLESTEROL (no ergosterol → no responde a azoles)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Responde a antiparasitarios (pentamidina, primaquina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Ciclo de vida","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"Forma trófica → se adhiere a epitelio alveolar tipo I","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"Forma prequística","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"Ascus/quiste → forma TRANSMISIBLE e infecciosa (5-8 µm)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"Patogenia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Reside exclusivamente en ALVÉOLOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"Beta-glucanos (pared) → inician respuesta inflamatoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"10","text":"MSG (Glucoproteína Mayor de Superficie) → variación antigénica → evasión inmune","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"10","text":"Macrófagos alveolares → fagocitos primarios (ALTERADOS en VIH)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"10","text":"Células T CD4+ → coordinan respuesta (DEFICIENTES en VIH)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"10","text":"Inflamación excesiva → daño pulmonar secundario","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología y\\NFactores de Riesgo","guid":"5kYHlp6t7qTmEptDjOk36Q","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"PRINCIPAL FACTOR: CD4 < 200 células/mm³ (o %CD4 < 14%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Mediana CD4 al diagnóstico ~20-50 células/mm³","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Transmisión","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Vía aérea (inhalación de ascus)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Transmisión persona a persona documentada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"Reservorios ambientales (aire, agua, suelo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"17","text":"Colonización","guid":"","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"0-20% adultos sanos colonizados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Colonizados = reservorios + riesgo de PCP bajo inmunosupresión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"Profilaxis en colonizados → selección mutaciones resistentes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"28","parent":"17","text":"Poblaciones de riesgo (VIH)","guid":"slg86iN8wsPfrMYvUaZVDg","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"No diagnosticados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"28","text":"Sin TARGA o TARGA inefectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"28","text":"Sin profilaxis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"17","text":"Poblaciones de riesgo (NO VIH)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Trasplante órgano sólido / células madre hematopoyéticas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"Malignidades hematológicas (leucemia, linfoma no Hodgkin)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"Glucocorticoides crónicos dosis altas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"Inmunodeficiencias primarias (SCID, hiper IgM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"32","text":"Desnutrición severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"17","text":"Incidencia → ↓ drásticamente con TARGA + profilaxis TMP-SMX","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"0","text":"Presentación Clínica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Inicio GRADUAL (días a semanas; promedio 3 semanas de síntomas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"VIH NEGATIVO → presentación más AGUDA y grave","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"39","text":"Tríada clásica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"FIEBRE (80-100%, a menudo >38.1°C)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"TOS NO PRODUCTIVA (95%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"DISNEA PROGRESIVA (95%) → esfuerzo → reposo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"39","text":"Otros síntomas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"Fatiga desproporcionada al esfuerzo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Escalofríos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"Dolor torácico no pleurítico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"Pérdida de peso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"39","text":"Examen físico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Taquipnea (60%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"Auscultación NORMAL hasta en 50% → NO descarta PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"Crépitos y roncus bilaterales (si presentes)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"51","text":"Candidiasis oral → coinfección frecuente, marcador de inmunosupresión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"39","text":"Hipoxemia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Gradiente Alvéolo-arterial O₂ (G A-a O₂) AUMENTADO >90% de casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Clasificación por gravedad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"LEVE: G A-a O₂ < 35 mmHg (PaO₂ ≥ 70 mmHg)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"MODERADA: G A-a O₂ 35-45 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"SEVERA: G A-a O₂ ≥ 45 mmHg (PaO₂ < 70 mmHg)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"56","text":"DESATURACIÓN CON EJERCICIO MÍNIMO → signo altamente característico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"39","text":"Complicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Neumotórax espontáneo (formación bullosa/neumatoceles → ruptura)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"Mayor riesgo con profilaxis pentamidina aerosolizada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"63","text":"Derrame pleural → raro (si presente, considerar otros diagnósticos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"39","text":"Pneumocistosis extrapulmonar (EPCP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Muy rara → VIH muy avanzado o profilaxis de segunda línea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Sitios: coroides, oído, tiroides, bazo, MO, ganglios, hígado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"39","text":"Mortalidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"VIH+: 7-20%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"NO VIH (presentación más fulminante): 29-60%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico por Imágenes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Radiografía de Tórax (RxTx)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"NORMAL inicialmente hasta 25%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Hallazgo CLÁSICO: infiltrados intersticiales difusos bilaterales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"Distribución perihiliar (alas de mariposa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"Patrón vidrio esmerilado bilateral y simétrico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"Menos frecuente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"Infiltrados lóbulos superiores (profilaxis pentamidina aerosolizada)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"Neumatoceles/quistes aéreos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"Neumotórax","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"74","text":"RARAMENTE: derrame pleural, consolidaciones (considerar otros dx)","guid":"JnvxEEaiyEujJDx26YSBHQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"73","text":"TACAR (TC Alta Resolución)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"Indicar si RxTx normal o no concluyente con sospecha alta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"Sensibilidad ~100%, Especificidad ~89%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":"Hallazgo típico: opacidades vidrio esmerilado bilaterales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Parcheadas o difusas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"Engrosamiento septal interlobulillar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"Neumatoceles","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"84","text":"TACAR NORMAL → hace diagnóstico altamente improbable","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"73","text":"Ultrasonido pulmonar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Emergente, útil en recursos limitados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"Artefactos en cola de cometa → correlaciona con vidrio esmerilado","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico de Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Muestras respiratorias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"LBA (Lavado Broncoalveolar) → MÉTODO DE ELECCIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Sensibilidad IFD >90%, PCR ~98%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Invasivo pero definitivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"96","text":"Esputo inducido (solución salina hipertónica) → primer paso no invasivo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Especificidad ~100%, Sensibilidad variable (IFD 55-90%; PCR 85-100%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"NEGATIVO no descarta PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"Esputo espontáneo → NO usar (baja sensibilidad)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"96","text":"Aspirados endotraqueales (intubados) → sensibilidad IFD 92%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"95","text":"Biomarcadores séricos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"LDH (Lactato Deshidrogenasa)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Elevada >90% de casos con VIH y PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"INESPECÍFICA → daño tisular pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"106","text":"Valor pronóstico: niveles altos o en ascenso → peor pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"105","text":"(1-3)-β-D-Glucano (BDG)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Polisacárido pared fúngica → coadyuvante diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"Sensibilidad 94.8%, Especificidad 86.3% (metaanálisis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"110","text":"Umbrales: >80 pg/mL o >200 pg/mL + PCR+ → sugestivo PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"110","text":"Falsos positivos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"Gasas quirúrgicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"Hemodiálisis membranas celulosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"IgIV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"Ciertos antibióticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"114","text":"Otras micosis invasoras (candidiasis, aspergilosis, histoplasmosis)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"95","text":"Microscopía directa (visualización quistes/trofozoítos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"Calcofluor White (CW)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"Fluorescente, rápida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"Sensibilidad 73.8%, Especificidad 99.6%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"121","text":"Requiere microscopio fluorescencia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"120","text":"Plata Metenamina de Grocott (GMS) → estándar histopatología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"Quistes color marrón/negro (pelotas ping pong aplastadas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"Sensibilidad 79.4%, Especificidad 99.2%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"120","text":"Giemsa / Quick Diff","guid":"","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"Visualiza núcleos y cuerpos intraquísticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"Quick Diff: Sensibilidad 49.2%, Especificidad 99.6%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"120","text":"Azul de Toluidina O (TBO): tiñe quistes azul, sens. 79.6-85.7%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"95","text":"Inmunofluorescencia (IFD/IFA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"133","parent":"132","text":"Anticuerpos monoclonales contra pared celular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"132","text":"Fluorescencia verde manzana brillante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"132","text":"Mayor sensibilidad que tinciones directas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"132","text":"Sensibilidad 48-100%, Especificidad 81-100%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"95","text":"NAAT (Técnicas amplificación ácidos nucleicos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"PCR → MÉTODO DE ELECCIÓN si disponible (>95% sens y esp)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"Dianas genómicas: mtLSUrRNA, DHFR, DHPS, HSP70, cdc2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"qPCR → cuantifica carga fúngica (distinción infección vs colonización)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"DESAFÍO: no hay umbrales cuantitativos estandarizados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"Propuestos: >9.655 copias/µL (no VIH), >12.718 copias/µL (VIH)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"LAMP → alternativa sin termociclador (recursos limitados)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"Sensibilidad ~87.5% en PCP confirmada","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"95","text":"Criterios EORTC/MSGERC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"PCP PROBADA: visualización directa (tinción/IF) en tejido o muestra respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"PCP PROBABLE: qPCR en muestra respiratoria + BDG sérico (descartadas otras micosis)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"95","text":"Combinación BDG sérico + PCR respiratoria → mayor VPP para PCP clínicamente significativa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Duración total: 21 DÍAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"Iniciar EMPÍRICAMENTE si alta sospecha (diagnóstico no se pierde: quistes/ADN persisten días-semanas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"Elección (GRADO AI): TMP-SMX (Cotrimoxazol)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"Dosis: TMP 15-20 mg/kg/día + SMX 75-100 mg/kg/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"152","text":"IV o VO, dividido c/6-8h (3-4 dosis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"152","text":"Enf. GRAVE (PaO₂ <70 mmHg o G A-a O₂ ≥35 mmHg) → IV inicial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"152","text":"Enf. LEVE → VO desde el inicio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"152","text":"Cambio IV→VO al mejorar y tolerar vía oral","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"158","parent":"149","text":"Alternativas (alergia, intolerancia, no respuesta)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"Primaquina 15-30 mg base VO/día + Clindamicina 600-900 mg IV c/6-8h (Grado BI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"REQUIERE TEST G6PD ANTES (riesgo hemólisis)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"158","text":"Pentamidina 4 mg/kg/día IV (infusión lenta ≥60 min)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"ALTA TOXICIDAD: hipotensión, hipo/hiperglucemia, nefrotoxicidad, pancreatitis, arritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"Reservar si otras opciones no viables","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"164","parent":"158","text":"Atovacuona 750 mg VO c/12h con alimentos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"165","parent":"164","text":"Solo enf. LEVE-MODERADA (menos eficaz en grave)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"158","text":"TMP + Dapsona (TMP 15 mg/kg/día VO c/8h + Dapsona 100 mg VO/día)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Enf. leve-moderada. REQUIERE TEST G6PD","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"149","text":"Corticosteroides adyuvantes (OBLIGATORIO en enf. moderada-severa)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"INDICACIÓN: PaO₂ < 70 mmHg O G A-a O₂ ≥ 35 mmHg O SaO₂ <92% aire ambiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"INICIAR dentro de primeras 72h del tratamiento anti-PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"Mecanismo: ↓ inflamación excesiva → ↓ daño pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"168","text":"Régimen PREDNISONA VO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"Días 1-5: 40 mg c/12h (80 mg/día)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"172","text":"Días 6-10: 40 mg/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"172","text":"Días 11-21: 20 mg/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"168","text":"IV equivalente: Metilprednisolona (~75% dosis prednisona), Dexametasona","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"149","text":"TARGA en VIH+","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"Iniciar dentro de las 2 semanas post-diagnóstico PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"Coordinar con infectología","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"Profilaxis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"PRIMARIA (prevención primer episodio)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Indicaciones en VIH","guid":"","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"CD4 < 200 células/mm³","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"182","text":"%CD4 < 14%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"182","text":"Historia de candidiasis orofaríngea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"182","text":"Enfermedad definitoria de SIDA","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"180","text":"SECUNDARIA (prevención recurrencia)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"Todo paciente con antecedente de PCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"Mientras persista inmunosupresión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"180","text":"Elección (AI): TMP-SMX","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"1 comprimido doble potencia (DS: 160/800 mg) una vez/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"Alternativa: 1 DS tres veces/semana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"190","text":"Alternativa: 1 simple potencia (SS: 80/400 mg) una vez/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"180","text":"Alternativas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"Dapsona 100 mg/día (+ pirimetamina si profilaxis toxoplasmosis). Test G6PD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"Atovacuona 1500 mg/día VO con alimentos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"Pentamidina aerosolizada 300 mg/mes (menos efectiva, no cubre EPCP ni toxo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"180","text":"Descontinuación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"CD4 > 200 células/mm³ SOSTENIDO ≥3 meses con TARGA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"Algunos datos: seguro con CD4 101-200 + carga viral indetectable ≥3-6 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"0","text":"Desensibilización a TMP-SMX","guid":"","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Indicar si alergia NO GRAVE (rash leve-moderado)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"CONTRAINDICACIONES: SJS, TEN, anafilaxia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"201","text":"Esquema oral rápido con dosis crecientes c/1h bajo supervisión","guid":"","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"Dosis inicial: 0.004 mg TMP / 0.02 mg SMX (suspensión pediátrica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"204","text":"Aumentar progresivamente hasta dosis completa (5-6 horas)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"Tríada fiebre + tos seca + disnea en inmunocomprometido = PCP hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"Auscultación NORMAL en 50% → NO tranquiliza (solicitar imágenes y G A-a O₂)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"207","text":"Desaturación con ejercicio mínimo es signo precoz altamente característico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"207","text":"LBA + PCR = mayor rendimiento diagnóstico (sens ~98%) → no dudar en broncoscopiar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"207","text":"BDG sérico es coadyuvante: útil si LBA no disponible o diferido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"207","text":"Iniciar TMP-SMX EMPÍRICO en enfermo grave (organismos persisten para diagnóstico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"207","text":"CORTICOIDES OBLIGATORIOS en PaO₂ <70 mmHg → iniciar en las primeras 72h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"207","text":"Primaquina + Clindamicina: siempre test G6PD antes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"207","text":"Colonización ≠ infección: PCR positiva no siempre es tratamiento (contexto clínico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"207","text":"No VIH con PCP = peor pronóstico (mortalidad 29-60%) → buscar activamente causa de inmunosupresión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"207","text":"Pentamidina aerosolizada profiláctica → riesgo neumotórax + no cubre sitios extrapulmonares","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"→ Infecciones Oportunistas VIH (Infectología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"219","text":"→ Delirium en UCI (Geriatría crítica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"219","text":"→ Manejo Ventilación Mecánica (UCI)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"1. Bateman M, Oladele R, Kolls JK. Diagnosing Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia: a review of current and emerging methods. Med Mycol. 2020;58(8):1015-1028.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"223","text":"2. Morris A, et al. Current epidemiology and outcomes of Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia in HIV-infected and non-HIV-infected patients. Clin Infect Dis. 2004;38(9):1310-1316.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"223","text":"3. Huang L, et al. An Official ATS Workshop Summary: Recent Advances and Future Directions in Pneumocystis pneumonia (PCP). Ann Am Thorac Soc. 2014;11(2):264-274.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"223","text":"4. Hof H. Pneumocystis jirovecii: a peculiar fungus posing particular problems for therapy and prophylaxis. Mycoses. 2021;64(6):586-594.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"223","text":"5. Panel on Opportunistic Infections in Adults and Adolescents with HIV. Guidelines for the Prevention and Treatment of Opportunistic Infections in Adults and Adolescents with HIV. National Institutes of Health. 2024. (disponible en aidsinfo.nih.gov)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":228,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"PCP Pneumocystis iPad","id":"map_830","resolved_references":[]}